  "category_subtitle": "Learn how to count cups and glasses in Japanese using 杯",
  "category_detail": "<b>Counting Cups in Japanese</b><br><br>In Japanese, cups and glasses of drinks are counted using the counter <b>「杯」(はい / hai)</b>.<br><br>This counter is used for <b>cups of tea, glasses of water, coffee, alcohol, and other beverages</b>.<br><br><b>Important Sound Changes</b><br>Some numbers change pronunciation when combined with 杯.<br><br><span class=\"example\">1杯</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(いっぱい / ippai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">3杯</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(さんばい / sanbai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">6杯</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ろっぱい / roppai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">8杯</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(はっぱい / happai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">10杯</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅっぱい / juppai)</span><br><br><b>Common Usage</b><br><span class=\"example\">コーヒーを二杯ください。</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(koohii o nihai kudasai)</span><br>Meaning: Please give me two cups of coffee.<br><br>This counter is very common when ordering drinks at restaurants or cafes.",
